title: The Girl Is Mine
subject: Rivalry
notes: First Star Vehicle duet i was aware of? Lead single from Thriller. first thing recorded during the sessions, Quincy said it was a red herring for what was to come. MJ wrote..after a suggestion from Quincy to write a romantic rivalry between two guys. Not a failure. no2 in US no8 in UK. super breezy bass, muted guitar and finger snap rhythm over a bed of real strings and synth flutes. Mac bass vox 2:44 Cocky McCartney the elder, not really bothered, but knows he'll win. the 'nurrgh..i've heard it all before' sigh before he lays down his tongue twisting truth that 'she told me that I'm her forever lover you know, don't you remember? tells us he is tired of this petty squabble, like an exasperated dad asked 'why?' one to many times. 'I DON'T BELIEVE YOU' . Dialogue outro. https://www.google.com/search?q=girl+is+mine+lyrics&oq=girl+is+mine+&aqs=chrome.1.69i57j0i512j46i20i263i512j0i512j46i512j69i60l3.11755j0j4&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8 Paul had disbanded wings and was readying the release of Tug of War https://www.the-paulmccartney-project.com/album/tug-of-war/ and had just released Ebony and Ivory two weeks previous to the recording Girl is mine and it was climbing the charts. Michael no big single for 2 years since Girlfriend penned by Macca, another cuckolding song https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pShTWUOsV64 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O8rc8FNCHcU Michael cold called Paul Christmas 80 just a few weeks after John was shot and proposed writing together (quincy has said he is a machevallian motherfucker) Say Say Say and The Man (santana-like guitar) recorded in May 81 but not released till Pipes of Peace in 83. https://www.the-paulmccartney-project.com/session/recording-say-say-say-the-man/ Quincy on MJ and PAUL https://www.vulture.com/2018/02/quincy-jones-in-conversation.html . Quincy and Spielberg ET storybook. Paul's Publishing advice https://www.billboard.com/music/rock/beatles-catalog-paul-mccartney-brief-history-ownership-7662519/ Dick James recommended by George Martin wowed Brian Epstein with his entertainment bizz contacts. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northern_Songs https://photos.google.com/photo/AF1QipP8OWPYkXUWaecUXm_Q_04aXL9ncAzkBLoSCG7i https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3jdB7Apk-R4&list=PLhrdp9uNV5z9LqoQ-wMIzZGyvKo49uX_T&index=8&t=12s , GG Reworking In 98 by Brandy and Monica. will i am remix 08 Sexual Healing intro, fat bass synth farts during the verse,cutting Mac and inserting his own banalaties 'she mine, she mine' 'like the way i rock' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0lJlNmAclPk came with MJ solo demo, more strings and longing reduced middle8 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eFWmSULkvXU 2 copyright infringement suits 84 https://www.leagle.com/decision/19841305594fsupp71111186 and 92. both failed MJ Deposistion https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c1uyuSB6Lm4&t=2320s and Copyright infringement summary https://blogs.law.gwu.edu/mcir/case/smith-v-michael-jackson/ The LP art MJ sketches/caricatures https://www.the-paulmccartney-project.com/song/the-girl-is-mine/

title: Two To The Power Of Love
subject: Attraction
notes: Only Released in Europe and UK Sept 84 as 2nd single from Janets 2nd LP. Terrible cheap cover thrown together, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two_to_the_Power_of_Love#/media/File:Two_The_Power_of_Love.jpeg Janet 17 studio promo shot juxtaposed with Cliff 44 shot in front of a hedge looking away to the right off the cover away from Janet, seems like a staged papparazzi shot. Produced by peak soundtrack Moroder (Flashdance, Scarface, Electric Dreams, Neverending Story) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XVvZ4-dTd64 Joe espositos scarface sing-a-long. The comedown after Moroder and Esposito's (with help from Donna Summer) disco triumph Heaven Knows https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BcHciz6eeeI Written by Pete Beckett and Steve Kipner. Why Cliff? Janet was trying to break free from Joe as he was guiding her career making artistic and commercial decisions (CLIFF?) she didn't want to be in Fame TV show. she eloped with James DeBarge of Debarge another family Musical group with a history of physical abuse, in September 84 but the marriage only lasted a year before annulment due to his pain killer addiction. Two of his brothers got done for drug trafficking in the late 80s. Cliff is hitting his silver jubilee and bases a release around it and does lots of TV with 'Please don't fall in love' and 'Baby, you're dynamite' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dG-uQswyZBA , a couple of duets just prior to this one rocker with Phil Everly 'She Means nothing to me' and one synth ballad with fellow gawd sqwuader Sheila Walsh 'Drifting' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=96Iqz-SGgL0 but maybe it is Cliff's success with ONJ in 80 with Suddenly from Xanadu, written by John Farrar of 'You're the one that i want' 78. Farrar uses Steve Kipner on ONJ Physical album 81, Beckett & Kipner joint songwriting credit ONJ Twist of Fate 83 bandmates from Tin Tin and then Skyband https://peterbeckett-player.com/credits Tin Tin were produced by Maurice Gibb. a studio session with Maurice Gibb doing a John Lennon impression was released as 'Have you Heard the Word' by The Fut in 70 as a fake beatles bootleg. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hXBZp_PvQjA https://peterbeckett-player.com/think-out-loud Beckett best known for his late 70s smooth rock band Player and hit song Baby Come Back https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hn-enjcgV1o Tried his hand at a duet a year previous with Beckett & Nelson https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cu1CGyrFmjo Featured on Fame (without Cliff) around time of release https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fmju6js6qyE After this she gets rid of Joe and starts working with producers Jimmy Jam & Terry Lewis of the Time band, who performed Prince Material.

title: Slow Rivers
subject: Break Up
notes:
Tough analogy to crack. Slow rivers run cold (dumb people are cold hearted?) shallow waters never sank so low (water would never degrade itself?). weather, water, dogs in fog. On a tv performance Cliff introduces it as Cold rivers to confirm the confusion, he doubles down during an interview "Elton and I made a record, a pretty good record too. It wasn't a hit. Did you hear that one? Elton John? It was called Cold Rivers. [sic] Good song. Good record, actually. But it didn't catch the imagination of the public. You know, that's the problem. But nevertheless it's a good record."
Cliff Richard http://www.cliffrichardsongs.com/popup.php?data=SlowRivers198410_popupplus also calls Elton ELT in a familiar way.. mid 70's Cliff released on Elton's label Rocket Records, Cliff was called ''Sylvia'' because he used to ring up the office each week, asking if his record had gone silver yet. So he got the name ''Sylvia Disc.'' Before Rocket Records Elton was a staff writer for DICK JAMES https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dick_James Cliff couldn't be hotter after the No.1 charity smash Living Doll with The Young Ones and Hank https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gGOU0o9K89g (cricket bats as guitars) and No.3 wallop 'All I Ask of You', a Duet with Sarah Brightman from brand new westend musical Phantom Of The Opera https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I45UVhxmMjY svelte perfect white suited Cliff, mini teddy boy dagger sideburns, smart and dangerous, prehaps imposing?.certainly superimposing. over sunsets, up sky fast action fluffy clouds, hair sniffing and fingering giddy twirling dancing across a tropical beach, 6 ft waves crashing behind 360 snogging. Elton on the decline after 85s Nikita. Leather Jackets not well recieved. 'I was not a well budgie, I was married and it was just one bag of coke after another.' This may of led him to join Barnsley's finest NWOBHM Act Saxon to play piano on Party Till you Puke from their 86 LP Rock the Nations https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leather_Jackets_(album) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elton_John_singles_discography . The lads are filmed Separately in Sydney(Elton) and London (Cliff) and mashed together with 'expert trickery' for Christmas Morning with Noel, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1X9bwh2881Q&list=PLhrdp9uNV5z9LqoQ-wMIzZGyvKo49uX_T&index=2 a 2hr simulcast from a decked out Telecom Tower (the inspiration for the NY party on the cruise ship in Bitter Moon, the dance kiss to Slave to love?) 'The first time family entertainment has been seen this way' the cross hemisphere link up being compounded by Noel's commonwealth BIG 2 knitted jumper. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u3vCk9dnUzI other guests included Maggie Thatcher, Rula Lenska and Dennis Waterman (also on DJM) (Dark glasses, shirtless under a big suit jacket christmas present ribbon tied round his neck drooping it's curls to mingle with his red chest hair. Child's head in one hand can of Fosters in the other, moaning about Auntie for not keeping a bar open for him. Fake snow fluffy along the embankment wall and sprayed up Cliff's tree trunk, Also a small undecorated christmas tree nearly cropped out of shot. Elton was Touring Australia and recorded with the Melbourne Symphony Orchestra for his follow up LP Straight after this within a week or so Elton had throat surgery to remove non malignant lesions from his vocal chords. He couldn't sing falsetto everymore. but he wasn't finished.

title: Don't Let The Sun Go Down On Me
subject: Break Up
performance_clip: Live recording, with SURPRISE guest... Originally released as an Elton John solo single in 74, another ambiguous struggling relationship song? But more of a pleading sense of urgency. First performed together at Live Aid 85 with errrr '...and Mr Andrew Ridgely' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ECN_wgw55lc George is very excited for his moment he looks suprised Andrew is on his tail. George added some backing vocals on Nikita in the same year. in 91 he performed his Cover to Cover tour, singing lots of.... covers. a couple of which were ELTs https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cover_to_Cover_tour George prefers control and makes use of the audience to up the spectacle with the unveiling 3 mins in https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RsKqMNDoR4o no conversation as a duet, just doubling of lines with ad libs, pretty faithful to the arrangment from 74, guitar harmonics in place (Davey Johnstone). But no Beach boys in the choir. Bettered the original release being a global hit. Before it George had not promoted his last album Listen Without Prejudice Vol.1. (What a turn off of a title, no wonder he rubbed people the wrong way) and not appearing in videos (instead employing supermodels https://www.biography.com/news/george-michael-freedom-90-song-music-video#:~:text=growth%20for%20Michael-,The%20%22Freedom!,referenced%20one%20of%20his%20Wham! ). Praying for time his Lennon 'on the nose' political anthem with subtitles on a black background echoing sign of the times but lacking style. hubris, Freedom 90 exploited the piano house electronic keyboards that Happy Mondays and Primal Scream had previously and going meta with the leather jacket from Faith image burning. After he had years of litigation with Sony that stifled his career until 96. Elton used his recently new lower range to his advantage with the following year's muscular duet Runaway Train with guess who....CLAPTON. Lethal weapon 3 credit song and maxi single with.... Don't let the sun AND SLOW RIVERS...Also George Michael had a 1988 US no.1 produced by Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis called Monkey

title: Heal The Pain
subject: Romance
performance_clip: Written in a Paul McCartney style. Released as a George 4th solo single in 1991 from Listen without... with less bongos, congos?. re released with mccartney to promote his 25th aniversary for the Radio 2 market? They sang Drive my Car together at Live 8 in 2005, maybe that is where he asked him?. He also performed Eleanor rigby and The Long and Winding Road at a charity gig 'Here There and Everywhere... A Concert for Linda' in 99 (which also features Jonny Marr doing his Morrisey impression on Meat is Murder. Him and Chrissie Hynde with lazy finger jabs of'getting the point across, prehaps with the Lyrics projected and the repeating of sentiment throughout they felt a little silly? Also culminating in a couple of songs by Paul, with an incredible sci fi sunset long sleeved Tshirt). It uses the chord progression from Eight days a week https://tabs.ultimate-guitar.com/tab/the-beatles/eight-days-a-week-chords-848333 , also similar to Isnt it a Pity. imagine him having big ideas but ended up doing it exactly the same cause he couldn't hear it any other way. i can get stuck on a song and no matter what you try it is lodged and logged as it is. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gFg13rHCF44 George talks of writers block. firstly during his sony litigation and later after his mother had died and the public toilet stuff (98) blew over. he no doubt had great respect for Paul as he was an incredibly prolific songwriter unlike himself. FLOP joke. Paul didn't release much in 2006. Paul at the time was going through his tabloid divorce from Heather Mills, being accused of being a drunk and wife beater from leaked documents. bear in mind both were victims of phone hacking to some extent. She said she got death threats. and the red tops scrambled for every saucy late 80's glamour photo. In 2007 he did the world a disservice by releasing the mandolin driven single Dance Tonight that i fear may of helped cause the second/third/fourth wave Ukelele craze of the 2010s.
